energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The problem requires finding the smallest positive integer n that is divisible by k and consists only of the digit 1. We can solve this problem by iteratively multiplying n by 10 until n becomes divisible by k. Since we only need to check up to log(k) iterations, the time complexity is O(log(k)). The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the variable n. The energy implications are low because the solution only involves basic arithmetic operations and does not require any complex data structures or algorithms.

